		<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
			<head>Biographical History</head>
			<p>Trial lawyer, b. 1933, and author of several articles and books on the administration of the American justice system.   He has written extensively on organized crime, the impact of the media on the legal system, and other current issues in the law.</p>
		</bioghist>
		
		<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
			<head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
			
		<p>The collection includes correspondence, case materials, book drafts, manuscripts and production records, television scripts for “The Courts,” reports and speeches, as well as an assortment of published articles and book reviews.  </p>
		</scopecontent>
		
